{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> | image = मनोहर पोथी.jpg | caption = Cover of Saran's work ''Manohar Balapothi'' | name = Acharya Ramlochan Saran | birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1889|2|11}} | birth_place = [[Sitamarhi]] [[Bihar]], India | death_date = {{death date and age|df=yes|1971|5|14|1889|2|11}} | death_place = [[Darbhanga]] [[Bihar]], India | occupation = Writer | nationality = Indian | period = 19th&ndash;20th century }} '''[[Acharya]] Ramlochan Saran''' (born February 11, 1889 in [[Muzaffarpur]], d. May 14, 1971) was a [[Hindi language|Hindi]] littérateur, grammarian and publisher. He founded Pustak Bhandar, a publishing enterprise, in [[Laheriasarai]] in 1915 and moved his publishing office to [[Patna]] in 1929. He also founded a number of magazines — ''Balak magazine'' (1926&ndash;1986), ''Himalaya'' (1946&ndash;1948) and ''Honhar'' (Hindi and Urdu) (1939).
==Educational work== His Hindi primer ''Manohar Balapothi'' attempted to teach the [[Devanagari]] alphabet to beginners. He also published ''Some Eminent Behar Contemporaries'' by [[Sachchidananda Sinha]],<ref name="bihar">Sachchidananda Sinha, [https://www.amazon.com/eminent-Behar-contemporaries-Pioneer-English/dp/B0007JJ45G/ ''Some Eminent Behar Contemporaries''], 1944, 218 pages.</ref> books by [[Mahatma Gandhi]], and other Gandhian literature in both [[Hindi language|Hindi]] and [[English language|English]]. He published ''Tolstoy and Gandhi'' by Dr. [[Kalidas Nag]] in English<ref name="kalidas">Kalidas Nag, [https://www.amazon.com/Tolstoy-Gandhi-Gandhis-foot-steps-Kalidas/dp/B0000CQWN8 ''Tolstoy and Gandhi'' ("In Gandhi's foot-steps" series)], 1950, 135 pages</ref> and produced a [[Maithili language]] version of the books of [[Tulsidas]]. Having edited and published ''Sidhant Bhasya'', a four-volume commentary on Tulsidas's medieval retelling of the [[Ramayana]], the [[Ramacharitamanasa]], he was first to start printing [[Maithili language|Maithili]] books in Maithili script ([[Mithilakshar]]).
He died on 14 May 1971 in [[Darbhanga]], [[Bihar]].
