{{Infobox language |name=Manao |nativename= |states=[[Brazil]] |extinct=18th century |ref = |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Maipurean languages|Arawakan]] |fam2=Northern |fam3=[[Upper Amazon Arawakan|Upper Amazon]] |fam4=Manao languages |iso3=none |linglist=qbh |glotto=mana1299 |glottorefname=Manao }}
'''Manao''' is a long-extinct [[Arawakan language]] of [[Brazil]]. The Manaos gave their name to the present-day city of [[Manaus]], the capital city of the state of [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]] in [[Brazil]].
Some words in the Manao Language include: {| class="wikitable" |+English-Manao Wordlist !English !Manao |- |One |Panimu |- |Two |Piarukúma |- |Three |Pialuky paulo |- |Man |Yrinály |- |Woman |Ytunalo |- |Sun |Gamuy |- |Moon |Ghairy |- |Water |Unüa |}
